;The Mozilla Foundation
Ri Mozilla Moloj


;The nonprofit Mozilla Foundation believes the Internet must always remain a global public resource that is open and accessible to all. Our work is guided by the <a href="%(url_manifesto)s">Mozilla Manifesto</a>.
Ri Mozilla Moloj, ri majun ch'akoj rutzeqelb'en, nuna'ojij chi ri K'amaya'l jantape' tok jun aj winäq tob'äl chijun ri ruwach'ulew, ri jaqel chuqa' okel chi kiwäch konojel. Ri qasamaj rojqan ri <a href="%(url_manifesto)s">Mozilla Manifiesto</a>.


;The direct work of the Mozilla Foundation focuses on fueling the movement for an open Internet. We do this by connecting open Internet leaders with each other and by mobilizing grassroots activists around the world.
Ri jujik rusamaj Mozilla moloj rojqan rutzuqik b'anoj richin jun jaqäl K'amaya'l. Niqab'än re re' rik'in kitunujri'ïl k'amöl taq b'ey pa ruwi' jaqäl K'amaya'l chuqa' kib'inisaxik ajxe' ajsamajela' chijun ri ruwach'ulew.


;The Foundation is also the sole shareholder in the Mozilla Corporation, the maker of Firefox and other open source tools. Mozilla Corporation functions as a self-sustaining social enterprise – money earned through its products is reinvested into the organization.
Ri Moloj yonil ya'öl pwäq richin ri Mozilla Moloj, ri b'anöy Firefox chuqa' ch'aqa' chik taq rusamajib'al rutzeqelb'en jaqäl taq b'itz'ib'. Mozilla Moloj nisamäj achi'el jun winaqel moloj ri nuto' ri' – ri pwäq nuch'äk rik'in ri taq rutikomal nrokisaj qa pa ri moloj.


